235	 * decode-rejection cases above (`AssetKey`, `IsoDate`, `HexColour`,
236	 * `ConferenceSlug`) already prove a bad value never produces a branded value;
237	 * these checks pin the *type-level* half of the guarantee so a future change that
238	 * silently drops a brand fails the typecheck (this whole block is a compile-time
239	 * assertion — the `@ts-expect-error` lines fail `tsc` the moment a raw `string`
240	 * becomes assignable to a brand again).
